## ğŸ§  Overview

This research explores how **blockchain** and **distributed ledger technologies (DLTs)** form the foundation of Web3 and redefine digital ownership through **fungible tokens** and **non-fungible tokens (NFTs)**.

---

## âš™ï¸ 1. Blockchain Infrastructure â€” 5 Major Examples

| Blockchain | Consensus | Key Features | Node Types |
|-------------|------------|---------------|-------------|
| **Bitcoin** | Proof of Work (PoW) | Pioneer decentralized currency | Full nodes, miners, SPV wallets |
| **Ethereum** | Proof of Stake (PoS) | Smart contracts, DeFi, NFTs | Execution + consensus clients |
| **Solana** | PoS + Proof of History (PoH) | Ultra-fast finality & throughput | Validators, RPC nodes |
| **Cardano** | Ouroboros PoS | Research-driven, energy-efficient | Stake pool operators |
| **Hyperledger Fabric** | Raft/BFT | Permissioned enterprise DLT | Peers, orderers, certificate authorities |

**Key takeaway:**  
Each blockchain relies on **nodes** for validation and **consensus mechanisms** for security, speed, and trust.

---

## ğŸ”— 2. Distributed Ledgers vs. Blockchains

| Category | Distributed Ledger (DLT) | Blockchain |
|-----------|---------------------------|-------------|
| **Definition** | Shared database replicated across nodes | A DLT that stores data in linked cryptographic blocks |
| **Access** | Often permissioned (private) | Usually public & open |
| **Structure** | Graph or other models | Chronological block sequence |
| **Consensus** | PBFT, Raft, BFT | PoW, PoS, PoH |
| **Example** | Hyperledger Fabric | Ethereum, Bitcoin |

**In summary:**  
> ğŸ§© All blockchains are DLTs, but not all DLTs are blockchains.  
Blockchains emphasize decentralization; DLTs focus on controlled, enterprise-grade collaboration.

---

## ğŸ’° 3. Tokens and NFTs â€” Redefining Ownership

### Token Types

| Type | Description | Example |
|------|--------------|----------|
| **Fungible (ERC-20)** | Identical, divisible, interchangeable | USDC, UNI, AAVE |
| **Non-Fungible (ERC-721)** | Unique, indivisible, one-of-a-kind | CryptoPunks, BAYC, NBA Top Shot |

Tokens are programmable digital assets that can **represent currency, rights, access, or identity**.  
They redefine ownership by using **smart contracts** that store and transfer digital rights securely on-chain.

---

## ğŸŒ 4. Real-World Examples

| Project | Type | Chain | Use Case |
|----------|------|--------|----------|
| **USDC** | Fungible | Ethereum, Solana | Stablecoin for global payments |
| **UNI** | Fungible | Ethereum | Governance token for DeFi |
| **CryptoPunks** | NFT | Ethereum | Digital collectibles / art |
| **Bored Ape Yacht Club** | NFT | Ethereum | Membership, branding, metaverse |
| **NBA Top Shot** | NFT | Flow | Licensed sports highlights |
| **Axie Infinity** | NFT | Ronin | Game-based NFT assets |

---

## ğŸ” 5. Ownership & Transfer Logic

| Aspect | Fungible Token (ERC-20) | NFT (ERC-721) |
|--------|--------------------------|----------------|
| **Identity** | Balance per address | `tokenId` ownership |
| **Transfer Function** | `transfer()` | `safeTransferFrom()` |
| **Record** | `balances[address]` | `ownerOf(tokenId)` |
| **Use Case** | Payments, governance | Art, gaming, identity |

**Ownership flow:**  
â†’ Mint token â†’ Assign to wallet â†’ Transfer updates on-chain â†’ Consensus validates â†’ Immutable record stored.

---

## ğŸš€ 6. Implications for the Future

NFTs and tokens are enabling **true digital ownership**, verified **without intermediaries**.  
They power use cases in:
- ğŸ¨ Digital art & collectibles  
- ğŸ¦ DeFi and on-chain finance  
- ğŸ•¹ï¸ Play-to-earn gaming  
- ğŸ§¬ Digital identity and proof of authenticity  

Together, they create the foundation of a **tokenized Web3 economy**.

